The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Monday, January 02, 2006 

 BRIEFS

 Durgapur, Jan. 1: A youth shot at Sukdeb Bhunia, 35, as he protested against the teasing of his wife at Mangalpur in Raniganj this evening. 

 Sukdeb is now in an Asansol hospital, about 220 km from Calcutta. The couple was returning home after a picnic.

 Calcutta: Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee said on Sunday many parents in the state were marrying off their minor daughters because of poverty. These girls often get lost and are never heard of again. Dowry is also being paid. Well have to check the menace through education, the chief minister told a gathering at Vidyasagar Mela.

 Burdwan: Three members of a family, including a two-year-old, were found dead in their house at Mangalkot, 160 km from Calcutta. Police said Swapan Pal, 35, a farmer in distress, and his wife Anjana, 30, probably consumed poison after killing Mithun.




